It is a behind-the-scenes look at how the engine is being built.


Engine Architecture
KSE is structured into three major layers:

1. Editor Layer
Tools for game creation:

Scene editor
Asset browser
Inspector panels
Scripting tools
UI panels and docking
2. Engine Layer
Core systems:

Renderer
ECS
Physics
Audio
Platform abstraction
Third-party libraries
3. Application Layer
Runtime components:

Game executable
Assets
Build output
Platform-specific deployment

Contrainsts

ConstraintType	|    Key Constraints
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Architectural	|    Layer separation, subsystem boundaries, platform abstraction
Technical	    |    GC behavior, real‑time rendering, ECS performance, networking security
Workflow	    |    Editor stability, GitHub branching, documentation accuracy
Scope	        |    Learning‑focused features, maintainability, avoiding over‑engineering
External	    |    Library compatibility, licensing, asset pipeline limits



