1 – Client Details 

1.1 – Statement of Intent 
This document outlines the full development process for KSE, a game project designed to expand my technical skills and deepen my understanding of modern game development workflows. The project builds on previous experience while introducing new challenges in programming, design, and online interactivity. 
1.2 – Purpose of This Document 
The goal of this documentation is to record the production process, explain technical decisions, and demonstrate the methods used to bring the project to life. It serves as a development log rather than a tutorial. 
1.3 - Project Overview 
KSE is a 2D/3D game engine editor that will allow users to create video games to their liking. This is intended to have safety data, expansion on all knowledge and engage with new information.
Focus Areas 
This documentation covers: 
Client requirements and theoretical research 
Security and data protection 
2D and 3D programming using C# 
Online systems and network interactivity 
Each section provides detailed insight into the development process. 
Tools and Technologies 
The project is intended to be developed using: 
C# 
Python and other Software Engineering lesson coding languages.
Visual Studio 
GitHub for version control 
Additional software for asset creation where required 
Target Audience 
This document is intended for assessors, future collaborators, and anyone interested in the technical development of Hazard Arena. 
 
1.4 – Aim 
The aim of KSE intended to make any game such as; fast‑paced, engaging game experience that blends 2D and 3D gameplay with responsive controls, dynamic environments, and online interaction. This project focuses on building a functional game while developing the core systems that bring it to life, including movement, combat, UI, and multiplayer features. 
1.5 – Goals 
1. Build a Functional Core Gameplay System 
Steps: 
Create player movement in both 2D and 3D spaces 
Implement basic combat mechanics (attacks, damage, hit detection) 
Add enemy or opponent behaviour 
Test and refine controls for smooth, responsive gameplay 
2. Develop a Polished Work Place Environment 
Steps: 
Design the layout of the arena 
Create or import 2D/3D assets 
Add lighting, effects, and environmental hazards 
Optimise the scene for performance 
3. Implement Online Interactivity 
Steps: 
Set up a networking framework (lobbies, connections, player syncing) 
Sync player movement and actions across clients 
Add matchmaking or roombased multiplayer 
Test latency, stability, and player limits 
4. Ensure Security and Data Protection 
Steps: 
Secure player data (usernames, scores, settings) 
Prevent unauthorised access or manipulation 
Implement safe data storage and transfer methods 
Test for vulnerabilities 
5. Create a Clear and Functional User Interface 
Steps: 
Design menus, HUD, and in-game indicators 
Add health bars, timers, and score displays 
Ensure UI works across different resolutions 
Test usability and readability 
6. Produce HighQuality Visual and Audio Feedback 
Steps: 
Add animations for movement, attacks, and effects 
Implement sound effects and background music 
Create visual cues for hits, damage, and interactions 
Polish transitions and feedback loops 
7. Maintain Strong Documentation Throughout Development 
Steps: 
Record decisions, changes, and challenges 
Include screenshots, diagrams, and code explanations 
Keep the document updated as the project evolves 
Reflect on what was learned during development 
8. Deliver a Playable, Stable Final Build 
Steps: 
Fix bugs and performance issues 
Run playtests and gather feedback 
Apply final polish to gameplay and visuals 
Package the game for distribution 

NOTE: This project will not be super smooth at all, and its main purpose is to build on my prior knowledge and gain new knowledge throughout the journey.
